The paper discusses the development of temporal compression for digital hardware SNN accelerators, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also focuses on energy-efficient event-driven computation, which is related to embedded systems (cs.ET) and hardware architecture (cs.AR). Additionally, the paper uses spiking speech and image recognition datasets, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
